<br>
P.S. About the topic.  <br>
I try to just help people who ask and make it clear what they want to do. Sometimes i do get bogged down and do have things id like to do on my own or may need help myself with a quest.  As far as im concerned i have no problems with anyone in the guild and ill help anyone who asks.  I wont avoid you or anything like that but i will occasionally say no when people ask.  I also (agreeing with nuv)  think that A. You should try to accomplish as much as possible before asking the whole guild to show to something.  and B. I am Big on telling you if i cant handle leading a raid.  for example: Everyone who has asked me to lead a poa or hate raid has met an answer of.....I dont know how to lead that, and they are both longer raids that will be hard to rally people to on a short notice.  Now if you ask for help in the hole....i own that place.  Ive wooped everyone at one point or another in the zone and ill be happy to lead.<br>
<br>
I also want to point out one Big thing Nuv said.  Please dont get disheartend or feel like the guild is against you because one of your raids didnt happen.  I always feel that RL comes first and ill walk away from EQ at the drop of a hat if something comes up even if im a leader of a raid.  My family and Job are too important to me.  Sometimes Extremely rare mobs pop up that would benefit the guild as a whole vs one persons epic. Sometimes we just wont have the amount of people needed and sometimes people just wont be in the right groove to raid.     Keep trying.  we will accomplish them all.<br>
<br>
-Twig <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#2F2F4F>- </font><a href=http://pub24.ezboard.com/bamazonguild>Amazon Guild Message Board</a><font color=#2F2F4F> - </font><a href=http://pub24.ezboard.com/famazonguildfrm1>General</a> <font color=#2F2F4F> - </font><a href="Http://www.xegony.org">Amazon Home Page</a><font color=#2F2F4F> - </font><br><br><br><br>Powered By <a href=http://www.ezboard.com/>ezboard®</a> Ver. 7.240<br>Copyright ©1999-2003 ezboard, Inc.</center></body></html>  

